= Video translation co-ordination =

There are two things you can do: translate, record a translation, or both. If you can't do the recording, you could still do the translation, so go ahead.

 1. Check below; you will find information about ongoing translations. If there is already an ongoing translation for your language, you can email the people who are making it in order to help them. Otherwise, send to prmat-help at ffii.org and wait for an answer. In any case, there are translation discussions at the prmat-parl mailing list, where it is a good idea to [http://lists.ffii.org/cgi-bin/mailman/listinfo/prmat-parl subscribe].
 1. Even more below is the text to translate.
 1. When the text is translated, either upload it here (preferably in another page linked to by this one), or, if this is somehow not possible, send it to prmat-help at ffii.org.
 1. Do the recording.
 1. Please '''don't''' send the recording itself to prmat-help at ffii.org; instead, put the recording on the web and only send the URL to prmat-help at ffii.org. If you don't have any means of doing so, ask at prmat-help at ffii.org for further instructions.

----

